	abstract = {Recurrent fuzzy neural network is widely applied in many areas because it combines the advantages of low level learning and high level reasoning. In considering the complicated factors and requirements for the Remote Operated Vehicle(ROV) control, petri network has been introduced to design a dynamic controller for underwater robot. It intends to reduce the computation burdens during network parameters learning. The gradient descent method has been used for online training. In order to guarantee its convergence, we have used the discrete Lyapunov function to determine its learning rate. The tank experiments have proved that the controller can adjust control quantity to reduce caculation and present strong advantages in the ROV robustness control. Keywords-Remote Operated Vehicle; Petri Network(PN); Recurrent Fuzzy Neural Network(RFNN)},
